<div class="clearfix"><div class="avatarholder"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/99b9251a5f566fe48215d28a4da2f91b?s=32&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ahousebythepark.com%2Fjournal%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2FHouse%2Fimages%2Fgravatar_default.gif%3Fs%3D32&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' /></div>			<div class="commentauthor"><a href='http://www.bluetickdig.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Alexis Gallisa</a> says:</div></div>
			
			<p>I use <a href="http://www.thenoodleincident.com/tutorials/typography/index.html" rel="nofollow">thenoodleincident.com</a> ems text sizing in many of my sites and have found that ems work pretty well with sIFR. </p>
<p>a bis set up of styles would be </p>
<p>body {<br />
font-size: 76%;<br />
/* font sizing in ems.  60%, 69%, and 76% are  appropriate smaller sizes */<br />
}<br />
h1 { font-size: 1.6em; }<br />
h2 { font-size: 1.4em; }<br />
h3 { font-size: 1.2em; }<br />
h4 { font-size: 1.0em; }<br />
h5 { font-size: 0.9em; }<br />
h6 { font-size: 0.8em; }</p>
<p>p {font-size: 1.0em;}</p>

			<div class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-3034" title="">#12</a> - February 28th, 2005 at 8:14 am </div>


		</li>

	
	
