		<li id="comment-3219" class="alt">
<div class="clearfix"><div class="avatarholder"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/b3b25dd27f8ef9be3fae97fbadfeed5d?s=32&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ahousebythepark.com%2Fjournal%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2FHouse%2Fimages%2Fgravatar_default.gif%3Fs%3D32&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' /></div>			<div class="commentauthor">StephenRS says:</div></div>
			
			<p>hi chris,</p>
<p>i was having the same problem a couple days ago. i placed the following css in my style sheet, and it got rid of the default browser text. good luck:</p>
<p>.sIFR-flash { visibility: visible !important; margin: 0 0 -50px -10px; }<br />
.sIFR-replaced { visibility: hidden !important; }</p>

			<div class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-3219" title="">#197</a> - April 15th, 2005 at 12:48 pm </div>


