		<li id="comment-3225" class="alt">
<div class="clearfix"><div class="avatarholder"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/dd05dde416d44c0d715f70065d95f4b5?s=32&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ahousebythepark.com%2Fjournal%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2FHouse%2Fimages%2Fgravatar_default.gif%3Fs%3D32&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' /></div>			<div class="commentauthor"><a href='http://mail.robertoscano.info' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Roberto Scano</a> says:</div></div>
			
			<p>Hem&#8230; if u add by dom elements and attributes that are not defined in the DTD used by the page, the page is not valid.<br />
If I use, for eg, tips that change a class=&#8221;blank&#8221; using DOM for change it in target=&#8221;_blank&#8221; this cause that the code of the page is changed (not the &#8220;show source&#8221;, but the real code send to the browser).<br />
The same is the sifir, that add  that isn&#8217;t a recognized element inside HTML/XHTML.</p>

